"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-05-paris-2024-olympics-wakama-reveals-motivation-for-dtigress-win-over-canada\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  D'Tigress head coach, Rena Wakama says defeat to hosts France motivated her side to go all out for a win against Canada on Sunday.  The six-time African champions stunned world number three Australia 75-62 in their opening fixture at the 2024 Olympic Games.  D'Tigress however lost 75-54 to France in the second game.  Nigeria rallied to beat Canada 79-70 to earn a berth in the quarter-finals.  \\\"I am glad we did have that loss because we were able to get back to what we do best. Also there is no pressure now on us and we have shown everyone that we deserve to be playing here,\\\" Wakama was quoted by FIBA.com.  The West Africans will face holders USA in the quarter-finals on Wednesday.  Heartland appoint Amuneke new head coach  Transfer: Man City striker ready to leave as Guardiola is offered Joao Felix  FIBA Women's W/Cup qualifiers: Wakama declares D'Tigress ready for battle  Wakama unveils D'Tigress squad for FIBA World Cup qualifier  AfroBasket 2025: Senegal can not stop D'Tigress' title quest - Wakama  AfroBasket 2025: Cameroon clash will be tough - D'Tigress coach, Wakama  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"